						<summary>

						<p>On two fragments of a slab lying near the temple of Chennakēśava.</p>						

						<p>SADĀŚIVADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>1547 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record is dated Śaka 1469 corresponding to 1547 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Mentions Kṛishṇarāya samu[dramu] and also refers to some gifts and taxes. Probably to the god Śrī Viṭhaleśvara. Mentions Kandanavōli-sīma.</p>						

						</summary>
